<quiz>
  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Application of linear motion in emergency braking</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>A vehicle is travelling along a straight road at a constant velocity of \({@v_initial@}\) m/s. The driver observes a hazard and has a reaction time (thinking time) of \({@t_thinking@}\) s before applying the brakes. Once the brakes are applied, the vehicle comes to a complete rest in \({@t_braking@}\) s.</p>

<ol>
    <li>Calculate the distance travelled during the thinking time (the period of constant velocity). [[input:ans1]]  [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]] m</li>
    <li>Determine the acceleration of the vehicle during the braking phase. [[input:ans2]] m/s² [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]] </li>
    <li>Calculate the total displacement of the vehicle from the moment the hazard was seen until it came to a stop. [[input:ans3]] m [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]] </li>
</ol>

<p><i>( Ensure you include the correct sign for acceleration.)</i></p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>
<p>1. Thinking Distance (Constant Velocity)</p>
<p>Since the velocity is constant during the reaction time, we use the standard speed-distance formula:</p>
\(\begin{align}
s_1 &= v \times t \\
&= {@v_initial@} \times {@t_thinking@} \\
&= {@ta1@} \text{ m}
\end{align}\)

<p>2. Acceleration</p>
<p>Acceleration is the rate of change of velocity. Given that the final velocity \(v\) is 0:</p>
\(\begin{align}
a &= \frac{v - u}{t} \\
&= \frac{0 - {@v_initial@}}{{@t_braking@}} \\
&= \mathbf{{@ta2@} \text{ m/s}^2}
\end{align}\)

<p>3. Total Displacement</p>
<p>The total displacement is the sum of the distance travelled while thinking and the distance travelled while braking:</p>
\(\begin{align}
\text{Total } s &= s_{\text{thinking}} + s_{\text{braking}} \\
s_{\text{braking}} &= ut + \frac{1}{2}at^2 \\
&= {@v_initial@} \times {@t_braking@} +\frac{1}{2} \times {@ta2@} \times {@t_braking@}^2\\
\text{Total } s &= {@ta3@} \text{ m}
\end{align}\)]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
